# .publicignore — paths removed from the public mirror (github.com/jakemercure28/sift-roles)
#
# Consumed by scripts/sync-to-public.sh. Each non-comment, non-blank line is a path
# (file or directory, relative to repo root) deleted from the staged tree BEFORE it is
# pushed public. The stage itself comes from `git archive HEAD`, so anything gitignored
# (.env, data/, .context/, node_modules/, jobs.db, *-cache.json) is already absent — the
# entries below are the tracked-but-private files plus belt-and-suspenders secret guards.
#
# This is a SOURCE-AVAILABLE core: the full application ships publicly (Postgres migrations,
# internal/auth, multi-tenant code included). Only secrets, deploy/infra, and private ops are
# stripped. Do NOT add application source here.

# --- Secrets (defense in depth; git archive already excludes these) ---
.env
.env.local
.env.selfhost.bak

# --- Deploy / private infrastructure (ThinkPad self-hosted runner, /srv/jsa) ---
.github/workflows/deploy.yml
scripts/deploy.sh
scripts/backup-sensitive.sh
scripts/backfill-events-from-sqlite.sh
docker-compose.staging.yml

# --- Observability stack (Grafana/Loki/Prometheus/Promtail for the hosted box) ---
observability

# --- Private deploy runbooks ---
docs/DEPLOY-thinkpad.md
docs/deploy.md

# --- Local backup / scratch artifacts (accidental/tracked; never publish) ---
.local-backups
_scratch

# --- Private dev automation (auto-PR into dev, local permissions/config) ---
.claude/hooks
.claude/settings.json
.claude/settings.local.json

# --- License is shipped deterministically as AGPL-3.0 by the sync script ---
# (private LICENSE is MIT; we must not let it clobber the public AGPL-3.0)
LICENSE
